{
 "name": "RPlog_Borderlines",
 "title": "Borderlines",
 "summary": "In the Sky Bar high above Cloud City, the Corellian xenoarchaeologist Paul Nighman meets the former princess Ylsa Estrallas to finalize a partnership. Over dinner and brandy they fence about trust and motives before Ylsa, seeking to escape the Hutt Ullo's grasp, agrees to lend her expertise to Paul's expedition for the lost treasure of the pre-Clone Wars Corellian pirate Darius Nul, said to lie beneath the ocean on Athaniss. Their alliance sealed, they share a long sequence of dances that strip away Ylsa's icy composure and kindle an obvious mutual attraction, which carries them out of the bar and through Cloud City to her residence. At her door the longing nearly overcomes them, but Paul gently pulls back, telling her they hardly know each other, must keep working together, and that there may be someone else in his life. Ylsa retreats behind cold professionalism, coolly listing the forged documents and intelligence she will need for their cover, and Paul departs with an apology for spoiling the evening, leaving her alone.",
